This gene plays a role in both cell-matrix adhesion and the organization of the extracellular matrix in connective tissues.

Human COL6A3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q37.3 and is approximately 90 kb in length. This allele, which encodes collagen alpha-3(VI) chain protein, is involved in beaded filament collagen formation. Mutation of the gene is associated with Bethlem myopathy, type 27 dystonia and Ullrich congenital muscular dystrophy.
Collagen alpha-3(VI) chain (3177 aa, ~344 kDa) is encoded by the human COL6A3 gene. This protein plays a role in extracellular matrix formation and cell-matrix adhesion in connective tissues.
